http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Fri 30 Oct 2020
Source: OIE, WAHIS (World Animal Health Information System), weekly disease information 2020; 33(45) [edited]
https://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=36327


Lumpy skin disease [LSD], Bhutan
--------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 30 Oct 2020 from Dr. Tashi Yangzome Dorji, Director, Department of Livestock, Ministry of Agriculture and Forests, Thimphu, Bhutan

Summary:
Report type: Immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 23 Sep 2020
Date of confirmation of the event: 5 Oct 2020
Reason for notification: 1st occurrence of a listed disease in the country
Causal agent: Lumpy skin disease virus
Nature of diagnosis: Clinical, laboratory (basic)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (7)
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 7
Outbreak cluster location: Samtse, Samtse (7 outbreaks)
Date of start of the outbreak: 23 Sep 2020
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Village
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Cattle / 1239 / 147 / 3 / - / -
Affected population: Outbreaks in small-scale backyard farms where cattle are let loose during the day for grazing. A few cases from a government farm within the affected area.

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Cattle / 11.86 / 0.24 / 2.04 / **
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter
**Not calculated because of missing information

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Unknown or inconclusive, vectors
Epidemiological comments: Symptomatic treatment -- antibiotic/antipyretics and wound dressing

Control measures
Measures applied: Movement control inside the country; surveillance outside containment and/or protection zone; surveillance within containment and/or protection zone; quarantine; disinfection; control of vectors; vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists); no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: Vaccination in response to the outbreak(s), vector surveillance

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Results
National Veterinary Laboratory (national laboratory) / Cattle / Real-time PCR / 5 Oct 2020 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreaks can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above].

--
